<h2>%%ReferenceStyle%%Electronic article, library database article</h2>
<hr>
<strong>REFERENCE LIST ENTRY</strong>
<br>
<br>
Add a reference list at the end of your essay citing all sources used in the body of your writing.
<br>
<br>
An electronic article retrieved from an online source uses the same format as a printed journal 
article with either the addition of a Digital Object Identifier (DOI), or the URL of the journal 
homepage. The 
<a href="http://www.crossref.org/guestquery" title="CrossRef &#45; Look up DOIs" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" title="opens a new window">
	DOI resolver
</a>
can be used to find a DOI from the citation details if it is not given on the publication. When 
no DOI number is available, do a web search to locate the journal home page or give the exact URL 
if freely available on the Internet. If a journal is only available via an archive database e.g. 
a discontinued journal available from JSTOR, give the home page URL of the database.
<br>
<br>
<strong>Format for articles with a doi</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	Authors. (Publication date). Title of article. 
	<em>Title of Journal, volume number</em>(issue number), page numbers. Digital Object Identifier
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Examples</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	<span class="hover" title="Authors">Bailey, N., Madden, C., &amp; Krashen, S.</span> 
	(<span class="hover" title="Publication date">1974</span>). 
	<span class="hover" title="Title of article">Is there a &#34;natural sequence&#34; in adult second language learning?</span> 
	<em><span class="hover" title="Title of Journal">Language Learning</span>, 
	<span class="hover" title="volume number">24</span></em>(<span class="hover" title="issue number">2</span>), 
	<span class="hover" title="page numbers">235&#45;243</span>. 
	<span class="hover" title="Digital Object Identifier">http://dx.doi.org/10.1111/j.1467&#45;1770.1974.tb00505.x</span>
</blockquote>
<br>
When the URL is not included as part of the doi, use &#8216;doi:&#8217; as a prefix:
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	<span class="hover" title="Authors">Smith, A., &amp; Brown, B.</span> 
	(<span class="hover" title="Publication date">2056</span>). 
	<span class="hover" title="Title of article">Dining out: A history of restaurant eating in Australia</span>. 
	<em><span class="hover" title="Title of Journal">Journal of Australian Historical Research</span>, 
	<span class="hover" title="volume number">3</span></em>(<span class="hover" title="issue number">5</span>), 
	<span class="hover" title="page numbers">110&#45;123</span>. 
	doi:<span class="hover" title="Digital Object Identifier">10.1108/13522750710740855</span>
</blockquote>
<br>
If there is no DOI assigned, use the URL of the homepage for the journal.
<br>
<br>
<strong>Format for articles with no doi</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	Authors. (Publication date). Title of article. <em>Title of Journal, volume number</em>
	(issue number), page numbers. Retrieved from URL of journal homepage
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Example</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	<span class="hover" title="Authors">Smith, A., &amp; Brown, B.</span> 
	(<span class="hover" title="Publication date">2056</span>). 
	<span class="hover" title="Title of article">Glamorizing domesticity: Narratives of marriage and motherhood in Desperate Housewives</span>. 
	<em><span class="hover" title="Title of Journal">Journal of Media Studies</span>, 
	<span class="hover" title="volume number">25</span></em>(<span class="hover" title="issue number">4</span>), 
	<span class="hover" title="page numbers">110&#45;123</span>. 
	Retrieved from 
	<span class="hover" title="URL of journal homepage">http://www.jms.edu.pk/<span>
</blockquote>
<br>
<br>
<strong>Format for articles freely available on the Internet</strong>
<br>
<br>
When an article is freely available on the Internet and if the URL is stable provide the direct 
URL in the reference.
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	Author. (Publication date). Title of article. <em>Title of Website</em>. Retrieved from URL of 
	article on the Internet
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Example</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	<span class="hover" title="Author">Cooper, D</span>. 
	(<span class="hover" title="Publication date">2009, March 31</span>). 
	<span class="hover" title="Title of article">Native ant may stop toad in its tracks</span>. 
	<em><span class="hover" title="Title of Website">ABC Science</span></em>. 
	Retrieved from <span class="hover" title="Retrieved from URL of article on the Internet">http://www.abc.net.au/science/articles/2009/03/31/2530686.htm?site=science&amp;topic=latest</span>
</blockquote>
<br>
<br>
<strong>Format for articles from archived database</strong>
<br>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	Author. (Publication date). Title of article. <em>Title of Journal</em>. Retrieved from URL of 
	database home page
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Example</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	<span class="hover" title="Author">Ramaley, R</span>. 
	(<span class="hover" title="Publication date">1916</span>). 
	<span class="hover" title="Title of article">Mushroom fairy rings of Tricholoma Praemagnum</span>. 
	<em><span class="hover" title="Title of Journal">Torreya</span></em>. 
	16(9) 193&#45;196. 
	Retrieved <span class="hover" title="Retrieved from URL of database home page">from http://www.jstor.org</span>
</blockquote>
<br>
