<strong>IN&#45;TEXT CITATION</strong>
<br>
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	Smith and Brown (2056) found that&hellip;
	<br>
	Alternatively: Recent research (Smith &amp; Brown, 2056) supports this view&hellip;
</blockquote>
<br>
When the authors are referred to more than once in the same paragraph do not include the date 
in subsequent references, as long as the work cannot be confused with others cited.
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	In a recent study, Smith and Brown (2056) showed that&hellip; Smith and Brown also found 
	that&hellip;
</blockquote>
<br>
If you are making a direct quotation, use quotation marks and include page numbers.
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	Smith and Brown (2056) suggest that &#34;the restaurant industry is on the decline&#34; (p. 111).
	<br>
	Alternatively: It was suggested that &#34;the restaurant industry is on the decline&#34; 
	(Smith &amp; Brown, 2056, p. 111).
</blockquote>
